  <faq>
    <item faq_id="faq_what_to_buy" question="What should I buy in the event shop?">
      <answer>
        <p>Always buy the lures available for silver tickets. They are worth more than they cost every time.</p>
        <p>Buying etched runes for your main builds is the main reason to play this event. Top etched runes include Arrow of Echoes, Elemental Crit, Meteor Split, and Potion Spring.</p>
        <p>Buying all the blessed runes is recommended. Progress toward unlocking all etched rune slots is always welcome.</p>
        <p>Mythic artifacts are a decent option once you have the etched runes you want.</p>
        <p>Do not buy keys unless you are playing for free. It is better to spend gems on keys directly.</p>
        <p>It costs roughly 37 keys worth of gems to buy one S tier gear. Not recommended unless it is a personal choice.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="faq_rank_rewards" question="What are the rank rewards?">
      <answer>
        <p>Your goal is to gain as much weight as possible early while keeping enough lures for later days.</p>
        <p>Below 50kg: first place gains 100 gems.</p>
        <p>Between 50kg-230kg: first place gains 200 gems.</p>
        <p>Between 230kg-500kg: first place gains 300 gems.</p>
        <p>Between 500kg-1000kg: first place gains 400 gems.</p>
        <p>Above 1000kg: first place gains 500 gems.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="faq_best_silver_lake" question="Which lake should I fish for the most silver tickets?">
      <answer>
        <p>Lake 4 (Polar Glacier) gives the most silver tickets per lure on average (~390 per lure). #data-lake_averages</p>
        <p>Its tickets per kg are lower than earlier lakes, but the average weight per lure is much higher, so you earn more silver tickets per lure overall.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
    <item faq_id="faq_line_breaks_pool" question="Does line breaking remove fish from the pool?">
      <answer>
        <p>No. Line breaking does not remove fish from the pool, so your pool counts stay the same while snapping lines.</p>
      </answer>
    </item>
  </faq>
